cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing, specifically the extraction of low-rank textures from 2D images in a 3D scene. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves geometric transformations and optimization techniques, which suggest that it could also fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of convex optimization and machine learning techniques could also place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
